00:00:39.640 --> 00:00:40.640
SNAKES!

00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:41.640
I’d definitely be atta that joint in a heartbeat.

00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:46.719
61% of people said they would bounce if they
saw cockroaches, but scientists warn that

00:00:46.719 --> 00:00:49.510
FLIES are actually twice as germy as cockroaches.

00:00:49.510 --> 00:00:53.179
And they’re specifically referring to those
pesky houseflies that can be found anywhere

00:00:53.179 --> 00:00:56.579
- after all, there are over 90,000 different
species of flies.

00:00:56.579 --> 00:00:59.350
So what’s the real deal on flies and food?

00:00:59.350 --> 00:01:04.489
Flies do gross things like eat garbage and
poop and rotting animal carcasses.

00:01:04.489 --> 00:01:08.500
All those germs from the gross stuff they
think is delicious gets transferred to their

00:01:08.500 --> 00:01:10.460
legs and small hairs all over their body.

00:01:10.460 --> 00:01:15.020
It only takes a second for them to transfer
those germs to your food or to your body.

00:01:15.020 --> 00:01:19.460
It’s also true that flies can’t chew,
so in order to eat, they spit enzymes on their

00:01:19.460 --> 00:01:21.840
food to dissolve it and then slurp it up.

00:01:21.840 --> 00:01:26.680
And yet another truth is that flies can carry
cholera, dysentery, and typhoid.

00:01:26.680 --> 00:01:31.479
But...notice most people DON’T get those
diseases...which brings me to the rational

00:01:31.479 --> 00:01:32.479
side of things.

00:01:32.479 --> 00:01:36.479
Flies that are festering on food can definitely
make you sick, so if there’s a bunch of

00:01:36.479 --> 00:01:40.299
flies feeding on a rotting apple - you probably
shouldn’t eat it!

00:01:40.299 --> 00:01:44.189
But when they land on food for a few seconds,
it’s unlikely that it’ll transfer enough

00:01:44.189 --> 00:01:45.590
bacteria to make you sick.

00:01:45.590 --> 00:01:48.130
It’s also a misconception that they poop
every time they land.

00:01:48.130 --> 00:01:50.970
That would be a lot of tiny fly bowel movements.

00:01:50.970 --> 00:01:54.929
They might spit or vomit on your food if they’re
intending to eat it, but it’s the bacteria

00:01:54.929 --> 00:01:58.770
that’s stuck to their body that actually
spreads disease and makes people sick.

00:01:58.770 --> 00:02:01.960
Long story short: fly vomit is your friend,
fly bodies?

00:02:01.960 --> 00:02:03.070
Not so much.

